               <msContents>
                  <summary>The first of two volumes, together with <ref
                        target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_7344"><idno>Persian MS
                           836</idno></ref>, of a Persian ornate prose paraphrased translation of
                     the <title>Mahābhārata</title>, completed by the Mughal poet <persName
                        xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="person_90041360"
                        ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/90041360">Fayz̤ī (ca. 1547–1595)</persName>. He
                     derived his work in turn from an earlier literal translation entitled <title
                        key="work_6910">Ramznāmah</title> completed by a team of four scholars to
                     which his younger brother, the Mughal minister Abū al-Faz̤l (1547–1595), added
                     a preface. An unidentified Mughal-era scribe probably completed this volume,
                     apart from the second by another hand, which contains the first six of eighteen
                        <hi rend="italic">Parva</hi>, in the <date cert="medium"
                        calendar="#Gregorian" notBefore="1750" notAfter="1800">late 18th century
                        CE</date>. </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_835-item1">
                     <author key="person_49232881" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/49232881/">
                        <persName type="standard">Vyāsa</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_6910">Mahābhārt</title>
                     <title xml:lang="sa-Latn-x-lc" type="alt" key="work_6910">Mahābhārata</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_6910">مهابهارت</title>
                     <title xml:lang="sa" key="work_6910">महाभारतम्</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="ar" type="basmalla"/>
                     <explicit xml:lang="ar"/>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>

                     <note>For two sets of the earlier literal translation with a preface composed by
                        Fayz̤ī's younger brother Abū al-Faz̤l held in the Rylands, see <ref
                           target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_26523"><idno>Persian
                              MS 1004</idno></ref> to <ref
                                 target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_26526">1007</ref> and
                        <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_26527"
                           ><idno>Persian MS 1008</idno></ref> to <ref
                              target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_26529"
                              >1010</ref>.</note>                  </msItem>
                  

               </msContents>
